Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
debugPtnBoundaryPorts(25.10)                      debugPtnBoundaryPorts(25.10)

Name
       debugPtnBoundaryPorts  -  The  debugPtnBoundaryPorts command prints out
       the boundary pins' debug information during partition in  a  log  which
       shows how to assign the power domain for the partition pins

Syntax
       debugPtnBoundaryPorts

       <-pins>

       The  debugPtnBoundaryPorts  command prints out the boundary pins' debug
       information during partition in a log which shows  how  to  assign  the
       power domain for the partition pins.

       This is useful when debugging CPF partitions as you get the information
       about  how  Innovus assigns the power domain for the partition boundary
       pins during debugging.

Parameters
       <-pins>
              Specifies a list of the partition pins. If wildcard * is  speci-
              fied, it means all partition pins.

Example
       Specify the partition pins(Hterm) you want to debug:

       debugPtnBoundaryPorts -pins "I2/d I2/clk"

       After  partition,  the  command  will  execute the partition command to
       print the following DBG info in the log file:

       DBG: deriving hterm I2/d power domain

       DBG: ....

Related Information
       Low Power Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

